The paper focuses on user mental models and perceptions of privacy threats surrounding voice assistants, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses privacy threats and interventions, which are relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and cryptography (cs.CR). The field study aspect of the paper involves the use of prototypes, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SI) or software engineering (cs.SD).
